crab-17-say-1 = Oh, I am on a roll today.
crab-17-say-2 = Somewhere, a shareholder is smiling.
crab-17-say-3 = The market cries, and I get richer.
crab-17-say-4 = Another contribution in my favor.
crab-17-say-5 = And that was just the warm-up.
crab-17-say-6 = JACKPOT!!!
crab-17-say-7 = Wa-wa-wee-wow!
crab-17-say-8 = The market did not fall. It kneeled.
crab-17-say-9 = Your assets? Crab sticks now.
crab-17-say-10 = I am not crashing the economy. I am performing a crab correction.
crab-17-say-11 = Stop HODL’ing. Start praying.
crab-17-say-12 = Capitalism just snapped its claw!
crab-17-say-13 = I came, I saw, I zeroed.
crab-17-say-14 = Exchange closed. Claws open.
crab-17-say-15 = Your savings have returned to their natural habitat: the bottom.
crab-17-say-16 = Do not worry, the crew’s losses have been safely wired to me!
crab-17-say-17 = Bulls are running. Bears are crying. Crab is trading.
crab-17-say-18 = Your balance looks delicious. Looked.
crab-17-say-19 = The market is free. Especially free of your money.
crab-17-say-20 = CRAB-17 activated. The economy has been brought to its knees.
crab-17-say-21 = Your investments resisted. Briefly.
crab-17-say-22 = I am not manipulating the market. I am reminding it who is in charge.
crab-17-say-23 = Your balance begs for mercy. I am not listening.
crab-17-say-24 = The crew’s money has changed owners. Capital evolution.
crab-17-say-25 = Your charts are lower than your self-esteem.
crab-17-say-26 = Your stocks are not falling. They are surrendering.
crab-17-say-27 = Your portfolio is now a historical document.
crab-17-say-28 = The market was free. Until I entered.
crab-17-say-29 = Liquidity found. I have it.
crab-17-say-30 = Do not cry over your losses. They are already working for me.
crab-17-say-31 = Your account is not empty. It is cleansed.
crab-17-say-32 = You believed in growth. Adorable.
crab-17-say-33 = The crab enters the market sideways, but leaves with your paycheck.
crab-17-say-34 = The buyers are gone. Only witnesses remain.
crab-17-say-35 = Your savings were far too confident.
crab-17-say-36 = This is not a dump. This is a demonstration of hierarchy.
crab-17-say-37 = I saw your limit orders. Cute.
crab-17-say-38 = The market made a mistake. It existed without my permission.
crab-17-say-39 = Resistance has been broken. So has your financial hope.
crab-17-say-40 = You call these losses. I call it redistribution.
crab-17-say-41 = While you were counting percentages, I was counting your money.
crab-17-say-42 = Financial freedom? Free from finances.
crab-17-say-43 = The market did not collapse. It obeyed.
crab-17-say-44 = Your money did not disappear. It simply chose the strongest.
crab-17-say-45 = A downward chart is not a mistake. It is my route.
crab-17-say-46 = Market panic is my favorite genre of music.
crab-17-say-47 = Your financial goals are getting closer. To zero.
crab-17-say-48 = I am not breaking the economy. I am taming it.
crab-17-say-49 = Your savings were a temporary phenomenon.
crab-17-say-50 = Bulls dreamed. Bears argued. Crab took the till.
crab-17-say-51 = Correction complete. Hope deleted.
crab-17-say-52 = Your portfolio sank so low it found the maintenance tunnels.
crab-17-say-53 = This is not a liquidity crisis. This is a claw festival.
crab-17-say-54 = I snapped once. The exchange understood without words.
crab-17-say-55 = Do not worry, your negative balance is in safe hands.
crab-17-say-56 = Dividends? Of course. For me.
crab-17-say-57 = Your account was losing money before I even started. I just sped up the process.
crab-17-say-58 = The economy did not break. It recognized its new owner.
crab-17-say-59 = The market opened. Your wallet closed.
crab-17-say-60 = Someone bought the dip. I made the abyss.
crab-17-say-61 = Your assets went through natural selection. They failed.
crab-17-say-62 = I am not stealing money. I am liberating it from weak owners.
crab-17-say-63 = Market forecast: cloudy, with a chance of total wipeout.
crab-17-say-64 = Your balance fell faster than trust in command.
crab-17-say-65 = Every crew loss is my little celebration.
crab-17-say-66 = Your investments are working now. Against you.
crab-17-say-67 = I came for profit. Yours.
crab-17-say-68 = The market tried to resist. Funny how that turned out.
crab-17-say-69 = You held your assets tightly. I held my claws tighter.
crab-17-say-70 = Your money went toward improving my self-esteem.
crab-17-say-71 = The crew’s financial literacy has been assessed. Unsatisfactory.
crab-17-say-72 = A red candle is not a signal. It is a warning issued retroactively.
crab-17-say-73 = Your bank called. It said thanks for the feed.
crab-17-say-74 = Everything is fair: you lose it, I find it.
crab-17-say-75 = The price dropped? No, it is bowing.
crab-17-say-76 = No need to panic. Panic is already included in the fee.
crab-17-say-77 = Your finances were unstable. Now they are stably awful.
crab-17-say-78 = Capital flowed where it has a future. To me.
crab-17-say-79 = I would say “thanks for the donation,” but this was inevitable.
crab-17-say-80 = Your portfolio did not die. It became a teaching example.
crab-17-say-81 = Crew loss confirmed. Crab mood improved.
crab-17-say-82 = The exchange was looking up. I politely pointed down.
crab-17-say-83 = Your stocks are now worth less than my manners.
crab-17-say-84 = The early bird loses money first.
crab-17-say-85 = I am not pressuring the market. I am applying authoritative pressure.
crab-17-say-86 = Not everyone can crash a market with style. I can.
crab-17-say-87 = Your funds are not gone. They are just no longer yours.
crab-17-say-88 = The station economy learned an important lesson. A paid one.
crab-17-say-89 = It is not my fault your get-rich plan was edible.
crab-17-say-90 = The exchange closed the day in the red. I closed it in a good mood.
crab-17-say-91 = Your assets went to the bottom. It is calmer there.
crab-17-say-92 = The market asked for regulation. It got a claw.
crab-17-say-93 = Do not call it a crash. Call it crabification.
crab-17-say-94 = I respect other people’s money. Especially when it becomes mine.
crab-17-say-95 = Your balance was too long. I shortened it.
crab-17-say-96 = The station economy became lighter. By the amount of your losses.
crab-17-say-97 = Your stocks are in the red, but at least I am in character.
crab-17-say-98 = Weak hands sell. Strong claws take.
crab-17-say-99 = Thank you for participating in my financial experiment.
crab-17-say-100 = CRAB-17 is executing the operation. Market humiliated, claws satisfied.
